senses.de: To complete a form by writing in the information that is asked for
senses.ex: Please fill out this application form carefully.

Tips.title: Interactive Context
Tips.description: Used when engaging with interactive documents requiring personal or specific information.
Tips.example: Remember to fill out your tax returns before the deadline.

Tips.title: Digital Forms
Tips.description: Increasingly common online; ensure all digital fields are completed.
Tips.example: You can't submit until you fill out all mandatory fields.

Tips.title: Attention to Detail
Tips.description: Be meticulous; inaccurate or incomplete information can result in processing delays.
Tips.example: I need to fill out this form accurately to avoid any issues.

senses.de: To become larger in size, appearance or character
senses.ex: As he became older, he started to fill out and look more mature.

Tips.title: Physical Growth
Tips.description: Often refers to a person’s body becoming broader or more muscular.
Tips.example: He started working out and really filled out.

Tips.title: Personal Development
Tips.description: Can describe someone's development in personality, skills, or confidence.
Tips.example: After traveling, she really filled out as a person.

Tips.title: Visual Impact
Tips.description: Can mean becoming more noticeable or having a stronger presence.
Tips.example: With her new role, she really fills out the stage.

senses.de: To make full or complete again by adding more
senses.ex: She filled out the vase with fresh water before placing the flowers.

Tips.title: Restore Fullness
Tips.description: Use when something needs to be returned to its original full state.
Tips.example: Can you fill out the candy jar? It's almost empty.

Tips.title: Household Use
Tips.description: Commonly used around the home for replenishing supplies or household items.
Tips.example: Please fill out the water pitcher when you see it's low.

Tips.title: Continuous Action
Tips.description: Describes an ongoing action to keep something always full or complete.
Tips.example: I fill out the bird feeder daily to attract more birds.
